ot;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e,","      \u003cspan class=\"pl-ent\"\u003e\u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e: {}","    },","    {","      \u003cspan class=\"pl-ent\"\u003e\u0026quot;cell_type\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e: \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003emarkdown\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e,","      \u003cspan class=\"pl-ent\"\u003e\u0026quot;source\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e: \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003eSpace X advertises Falcon 9 rocket launches on its website with a cost of 62 million dollars; other providers cost upward of 165 million dollars each, much of the savings is because Space X can reuse the first stage. Therefore if we can determine if the first stage will land, we can determine the cost of a launch. This information can be used if an alternate company wants to bid against space X for a rocket launch.   In this lab, you will create a machine learning pipeline  to predict if the first stage will land given the data from the preceding labs.\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e,","      \u003cspan class=\"pl-ent\"\u003e\u0026quot;metadata\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e: {}","    },","    {","      \u003cspan class=\"pl-ent\"\u003e\u0026quot;cell_type\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e: \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003emarkdown\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e,","      \u003cspan class=\"pl-ent\"\u003e\u0026quot;source\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e: \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e![](https://cf-courses-data.s3.us.cloud-object-storage.appdomain.cloud/IBMDeveloperSkillsNetwork-DS0701EN-SkillsNetwork/api/Images/landing_1.gif)\u0